<TITLE> Grant Luden set to become Tiger trainer </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 16 (bdnews24.com)  Grant Trafford Luden is all set to become the national cricket team's trainer as the South African joined the Tigers on the first day of training Monday for the coming Asia Cup, scheduled for June 24 to July 6 in Pakistan. "We are yet to sign any deal, but will soon do so with him for two years and it will be effective from the Bangladesh tour of Pakistan for the Asia Cup," said BCB cricket operation committee chairman Gazi Ashraf Hossain Lipu. Shane McDermott left the Bangladesh national cricket team's trainer post vacant for two months, leaving after Bangladesh's home series against South Africa in the middle of March. The Australian, McDermott was temporarily appointed the Tigers' trainer following the departure of his compatriot Paul Chapman, who left here for Australia before Bangladesh tour of New Zealand in December last. bdn
